From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Dynamic Devices <support@dynamicdevices.co.uk>
Date: Wed, 11 Jun 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] ASoC: pcm6240: do not replay PRE_POWER_UP on capture startup (DT510)

0003 runs pcmdevice_mute(unmute) on every capture open, which replays the full
regbin PRE_POWER_UP block including Ch1 Digi (0x52=0xf0). That resets amixer
and i2cset gain changes made before arecord and makes Ch1 Digi appear broken.

ASI bring-up is already handled by pcmdevice_asi_capture_enable (0004). Skip
PRE_POWER_UP on stream startup; keep PRE_SHUTDOWN on shutdown for power-down.

Signed-off-by: Dynamic Devices <support@dynamicdevices.co.uk>
---
 sound/soc/codecs/pcm6240.c | 4 ++--
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

diff --git a/sound/soc/codecs/pcm6240.c b/sound/soc/codecs/pcm6240.c
--- a/sound/soc/codecs/pcm6240.c
+++ b/sound/soc/codecs/pcm6240.c
@@ -2015,10 +2015,10 @@ static int pcmdevice_startup(struct snd_pcm_substream *substream,
 			     struct snd_soc_dai *dai)
 {
 	if (substream->stream == SNDRV_PCM_STREAM_CAPTURE) {
-		int ret = pcmdevice_mute(dai, 0, SNDRV_PCM_STREAM_CAPTURE);
-
-		return ret ? ret : pcmdevice_asi_capture_enable(dai, true);
+		return pcmdevice_asi_capture_enable(dai, true);
 	}
 
 	return 0;
 }
